[normal]Vehicle technology is advancing quickly, and systems that interact with their surroundings and with other vehicles are becoming increasingly common. These technologies create the opportunity for vehicles that can autonomously manage actions that are currently reserved for the driver and could, in the future, be able to carry out all of the driver tasks. The UK has a fantastic opportunity to be at the forefront of these developments”
[normal] – Para 3.39, Action for Roads, 
[normal]Command Paper Cm 8679, 
[normal]DfT
[normal] July 2013 
