[normal]“On environmental grounds, the new line (between Cologne and the Rhine/Main conurbation) was generally constructed in parallel with an existing motorway, as close to it as possible. For this reason, the maximum gradient was set at 40%, minimum track radius at 3350m and maximum cant at 170mm, which allows a design speed of 300 km/hr around curves.” 
[normal] - 
[normal]Dr.Ing
[normal]. 
[normal]Eberhard
[normal] 
[normal]Jaensch
[normal], Network Strategy Unit, DB 
[normal]Netz
[normal] AG, Railway Technical Review 2/05
