[normal]“The preferred route of HS2 crosses the Chilterns AONB at its widest point, in contradiction to the policy followed by HS1. In Kent, the route of HS1 was amended to avoid the AONB … and run beside the existing M20, a major strategic transport corridor which reduced incremental noise pollution and landscape damage. By contrast, HS2 appears to have been deliberately routed through the least spoilt, widest part of the Chilterns” 
[normal]– Steve Baker MP, Westminster Hall debate 23rd November 2010 
[normal]http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101123/halltext/101123h0001.htm#10112319000001
