[normal]“
[normal]Maria Eagle
[normal]:[bold] To ask the Secretary of State for Transport whether any changes have been made on expenditure on High Speed 2 since the figures set out in the 2010 spending review. [146109]
[normal]Mr
[normal] Simon Burns:
[normal] As part of the Government's comprehensive spending review in 2010, £773 million was allocated to the development of the High Speed 2 Project. This has increased to around £900 million, primarily due to an increase in the capital budget relating to property compensation. This increase reflects the forthcoming introduction, subject to the outcome of the recent consultation, of long-term discretionary and statutory compensation schemes for Phase One. The increase in budget was notified to HM Treasury as part of the Department's main estimate submissions at the beginning of
[normal] 
[normal]2012”
[normal] – Written Questions 6
[normal]th
[normal] March 2013, 
[normal]http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201213/cmhansrd/cm130306/text/130306w0001.htm
